15, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9801642680553895, \"rank\": 0.0193078353410833, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The West\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"its small brothers\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1038}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking back now, China and the US-led West have staged a thrilling \\\"life and death speed\\\".\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1071, \"end\": 1076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998149564547531, \"rank\": 0.0017755992329551169, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the US-led West\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"a thrilling \\\"life and death speed\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If China's power growth is even a step slower, it will be reaped as cruelly as the former Soviet Union.\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1148, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998149564547531, \"rank\": 0.0017755992329551169, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1242, \"end\": 1247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999958631633, \"rank\": 2.3688895584833517e-09, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, when the West was ready to harvest China, it suddenly found that China had transformed into the strongest industrial country and could not harvest China as it had harvested the Soviet Union.\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998149564547531, \"rank\": 0.0017755992329551169, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1323, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998149564547531, \"rank\": 0.0017755992329551169, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1405, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998149564547531, \"rank\": 0.0017755992329551169, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1442, \"end\": 1447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999958631633, \"rank\": 2.3688895584833517e-09, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1271}, {\"ngram\": \"the strongest industrial country\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1382}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To wage war against China, the world's most powerful industrial country with 1.4 billion people, 9.6 million square kilometers of land and the centralized leadership of the Communist Party is beyond the scope of experience and imagination of the entire West.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998149564547531, \"rank\": 0.0017755992329551169, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1461}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's most powerful industrial country\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"1.4 billion people\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"9.6 million square kilometers\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1576}, {\"ngram\": \"land\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"the centralized leadership\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"the Communist Party\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1638}, {\"ngram\": \"the scope\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"experience\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1672}, {\"ngram\": \"imagination\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire West\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1707}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the West cannot solve its internal crisis if it cannot plunder resources from the outside through war.\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"its internal crisis\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"resources\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"the outside\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1803}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unable to resolve its internal crisis, the West languishes helplessly.\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1888, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its internal crisis\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1855}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This takes the form of running down the road to legalizing drug use, bungee jumping in gender-diverse (up to a hundred) fields, and so on.\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 2027, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the form\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1908}, {\"ngram\": \"the road\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1933}, {\"ngram\": \"drug use\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1956}, {\"ngram\": \"bungee jumping\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"up to a hundred) fields\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, decadence has become a mainstream culture in the West, and it was showcased to great fanfare to the world at the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2190, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"decadence\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2047}, {\"ngram\": \"a mainstream culture\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2079}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"great fanfare\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2143}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2167}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was so shocking that the whole world, including the Western world itself, was so shocked that the official website of the Olympic Organizing Committee hurriedly removed the video of the opening ceremony and publicly apologized to the world.\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2246, \"end\": 2253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9999914681107099, \"rank\": 8.531526766619389e-06, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the whole world\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"the official website\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2308}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Organizing Committee\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"the video\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2372}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2396}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\